title: Keydous NJ80 keyboard review (Gateron Pro Yellow)

media:group.media:title: Keydous NJ80 keyboard review (Gateron Pro Yellow)
media:group.media:description:
Skip to 11:45 for a typing demonstration. 
Today we look at a mid-budgete hotswap chassis, the Keydous NJ80, as well as Gateron Pro switches, their updated line of MX clone switches. Hope you enjoy the video!

Intro by Kyle Carter
Outro by Facundo Cabanne

Follow me on Twitter for updates on my keyboard videos! https://twitter.com/chyrosran22

The practice sentence was: "Hello my name is Thomas and I'm typing on a Keydous NJ80 right now. This is not that bad of a keyboard, simple, but elegant, and it works reasonably well!"
